Business Brief -- Mars Inc.:
   Candy Company Introduces
   Lower-Calorie Milky Way
At a news conference at the trendy Spago restaurant in
West Hollywood, Calif., MM/Mars said its new bar has 190
calories, 25% fewer calories than a regular Milky Way and 50%
fewer calories from fat.
   Milky Way II, under development for five years and made
with a reduced-calorie fat developed by Procter  Gamble Co.,
will be available beginning in April. Initial distribution is
planned only in California, Idaho, Nevada, Oregon,
Washington, Alaska and Hawaii.